Part of my creative process very often includes fire and a SIGIL. It’s why I post my work on fire so often. When I do metal work I first create a sigil on a piece of paper. Then I verbalize what was on the paper. Then I light my forge or torch and begin moulding the metal from the fire created from the sigil. When I’m writing a song. After the lyrics have been completed. I vocalize the lyrics (singing). And then I write the lyrics on a piece of paper and burn them. Sigils are incredibly powerful manifestation excersises. They set into motion your intention. Verbalizing these intentions casts them into the cosmos Eternally. As they resonate they reform matter at a molecular level. Taking form from your intentions. This is the bridge between the metaphysical and the physical world. And why thoughts and words are so powerful. Once set into motion there’s no going back. 
#sigil 
A sigil (/ˈsɪdʒəl/; pl. sigilla or sigils) is a type of symbol used in magic. The term has usually referred to a type of pictorial signature of an angel or other entity. In modern usage, especially in the context of chaos magic, sigil refers to a symbolic representation of the magician's desired outcome.

Origin

late 16th century (denoting a phantom or ghost): from Latin, literally ‘shade’.
